ols. The neighborhoods are full of it, of course it's not going to just stop at the school gates, that's ridiculous to think so. Just moving these kids to a private school isn't going to turn them into model citizens, in fact most private schools would take one look at them and boot them out on the streets after the first incident. If you want better schools, create better neighborhoods. If you want better students, create better adults to produce them. Sure, there are problems with the schools, nobody denies that, but to say that a private institution is the magical solution to all the problems is just ludicrous. So long as you have students addicted to drugs, members of gangs and commiting crimes, you will have all these problems in any school they attend. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1076" language="en" documentId="4788" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Cephus" date="7th November 2006 01:17 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=12481&amp;page=6" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4788" notes="" title="Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1076"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>